<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - 3300 Model - MULTIPLEXING (DATA LINKS) - DATA LINK REPAIR -
        J1939
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="9">
        <title>J1939</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Repairs to damaged J1939 circuits should be accomplished using similar types of wiring. Splices should
                be crimped, soldered and covered with heat shrink. Insure the twist in the wire pair is maintained and
                that any wire bundles in the engine compartment are shielded and covered with heat shrink.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Wire Repair</title>
            <para>This instruction addresses termination and splicing of J1939 wire.</para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always turn off power to any electrical circuit before starting work.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Incorrect Connection or splicing of J1939 wire may result in compromise of function.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <title>Preparation of J1939 wire for connection.</title>
            </para>
            <figure id="f08298311" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298311.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>J1939 Twisted Pair Wire</caption>
            </figure>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Strip back outer shield 3 1/8 in. (76 mm).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Strip green wire and yellow wire 1/4 in. (6.35mm) being careful not to cut individual strands.
                        Re-twist the wires if they have separated.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Install terminals on the wire ends, and crimp.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>The 1/4" heat shrink tube will be shrunk later after the wires have been inserted into the
                        connector.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <para>
                <title>Wiring the Connector</title>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>The wires must be installed in the correct cavities. Refer to following Figure.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f08298312" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298312.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>J1939 Terminating Resistor Connector</caption>
            </figure>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Yellow wire inserts to position A.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Plug inserts to position B.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Green wire inserts to position C.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Be sure that the connector pins are fully seated (locked) in the connector. If pins are fully
                        seated, they will not pull back out with moderate pressure.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>After pins are seated they can only be released by depressing the pin lock (red plastic) at
                        the front side of the connector.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f08298313" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298313.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>J1939 Terminating Resistor and Connector</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>A. CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>B. TERMINATING RESISTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Wire Splicing</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Strip wire ends 1/4 inch.</para>
                <figure id="f08298314" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298314.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption></caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-twist any loose wire strands</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide 2 inch pieces of heat shrink tube over wire for later use.</para>
                <figure id="f08298315" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298315.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption></caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert ends of wires into splice joint and crimp.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Solder the wires and crimp joint together.</para>
                <figure id="f08298316" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298316.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption></caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Center heat shrink tube over splice and shrink.</para>
                <figure id="f08298317" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298317.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption></caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wrap wires with electrical tape or heat shrink tubing. Maintain at least 1/2 wrap
                    overlap.
                </para>
                <figure id="f08298318" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298318.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption></caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Once electrical tape or heat shrink tubing is in place, there should be no exposed
                    wires.
                </para>
                <figure id="f08298319" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg08/G08298319.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption></caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
